    "recap_headline": "Brown University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SOUTH ORANGE, N.J. \u2013\nA furious four-run ninth inning rally lifted the Brown baseball team to a 9-6 win over Seton Hall on Saturday afternoon.\nFreshman\nCamren Piwnicki\nearned his first collegiate win after throwing 5.0 strong shutout innings of relief, allowing just three hits and two walks with three strikeouts. Senior\nMika Petersen\nwent 4-for-5 at the plate with a run and two RBIs. Senior\nDJ Dillehay\nadded three hits and an RBI, sophomore\nAlex Benevento\nhad two hits, including the game-tying double in the ninth, and senior\nLogan Meusy\nscored three runs and delivered the game-winning hit with two outs in the ninth.\nSenior\nChristian Keel\nlocked down his second save of the season with a scoreless ninth.\nMuch of the damage for both teams came in the second and third innings. The Bears jumped out to a 3-0 lead in the second when Meusy walked, stole second and scored on a wild pitch.\nAndrew Hanlon\nlaid down a bunt on a squeeze play for a run, and\nAlex Mihailovich\ndrove in Petersen with a two-out single.\nAfter SHU tied it with three runs on three hits in the bottom of the inning, Brown got two runs right back in the third to take a 5-3 lead. Benevento led off with a triple and scored on a single by Dillehay, and Petersen later drove in Meusy with an infield single.\nSeton Hall plated three more runs in the bottom of the third, two of which we unearned, to take a 6-5 lead, which they held into the ninth inning.\nFive hits in the ninth, including three doubles, sparked the Brown comeback. Benevento tied the game with a one-out double over the left fielder's head. Two batters later, Meusy doubled to left-center to plate Benevento with what proved to be the winning run. Petersen added a double of his own to plate Meusy with an insurance run, and\nJack Edmunds\nadded an RBI single to push the lead to 9-6.\nTIED UP IN THE NINTH!!!!!\nBenevento smacks this double to left field to tie the game 6-6! Go-ahead run now on 2nd with 1 out!\npic.twitter.com/5pcy0fFD1l\n\u2014 Brown Baseball (@BrownU_Baseball)\nMarch 14, 2026\nTwo-out magic for the lead!!! Meusy sends this double to left field to score Benevento and give Brown the lead!\n7-6 Bears and still batting in the 9th\npic.twitter.com/4gnnNY6vA7\n\u2014 Brown Baseball (@BrownU_Baseball)\nMarch 14, 2026\nFOURTH hit of the game for\nMika Petersen\nto extend the lead! Brown's third RBI double of the inning and it's now an 8-6 lead in the 9th!\npic.twitter.com/dC5nUsUTlJ\n\u2014 Brown Baseball (@BrownU_Baseball)\nMarch 14, 2026\nThe Bears and Pirates will finish off their three-game weekend series with the rubber game on Sunday. First pitch is set for noon and will be streamed live on YouTube.\nBROWN UNIVERSITY SPORTS FOUNDATION\nThe Brown University Sports Foundation (BUSF) is the backbone of our athletics program, playing a crucial role in enhancing the student-athlete experience.\u00a0This\u00a0is possible through philanthropic support from our alumni, parents, fans, and friends.\u00a0Your\u00a0gift through the Sports Foundation can immediately impact today's Brown Bears, helping them excel in the classroom, in competition, and, most importantly, in the community. Please click\nhere\nto learn more about how\u00a0you\u00a0can support the Bears.\nFOLLOW US ON SOCIAL\nFor the latest on Brown Athletics, please follow\n@BrownU_Bears\non X and\n@BrownU_Bears\non Instagram. Like\nBrownUBears\non Facebook and subscribe to the\nBrownAthletics\nYouTube channel."
  },
